habitat_description: The Fog Shrew (Sorex sonomae) prefers damp, marshy, or brushy areas within Douglas Fir and redwood forests, wet meadows, and emergent freshwater wetlands, but has also been found in redwood forests, dense spruce forests, dense chaparral, montane riparinan areas, and hardwood-conifer habitats (Zeinner et al. 2000).
